  "instructions": [
    "Mix all the marinade ingredients in a bowl until combined. Add the chicken thighs, coat well, and cover. Leave to marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Blitz the green chilli, mint leaves, coriander, olive oil and a splash of water in a food processor until smooth. Transfer to a bowl and mix with plain yoghurt, garlic, cumin, garam masala, and lemon juice.",
    "Remove the chicken from the fridge 10 minutes before cooking. Heat a non-stick pan, and cook the thighs on each side for about 5 minutes. Once fully cooked, remove from the pan and set aside.",
    "Add the peppers to the same pan skin-side down, and cook until slightly soft and charred.",
    "Slice the cooked chicken into thin strips. Spread a generous amount of mint yoghurt sauce on to a warm flatbread. Layer with the chicken, peppers, red onion and tomatoes. Top with a teaspoon of mango chutney and a sprinkle of fresh coriander. Wrap, and tuck in."
